%I A393497 #26 Mar 23 2026 18:26:57
%S A393497 1,2,1,3,16,1,2,3,5,8,24,6,640,3,7,4,40,1,195,32,3,534000,39,1,9,42,
%T A393497 106000,5,3,12754704,40,10,8,6525,226592,2,273,2968,15,6,1039424,1,16,
%U A393497 48,305,6,4,3621,1856,1,2,531,13,9384,126585,3588,1360,7,896073208080,56
%N A393497 Let K be the real quadratic field of discriminant A003658(n). Then a(n) is the index in O_K of the quadratic order generated by units in O_K with norm 1.
%C A393497 Let epsilon be the fundamental unit of K, then the quadratic order is Z[epsilon] if epsilon has norm 1, and Z[epsilon^2] is epsilon has norm -1.
%C A393497 If (x0,y0) is the smallest positive solution to x^2 - D*y^2 = 4, D = A003658(n), then a(n) = y0.
%H A393497 Jianing Song, <a href="/A393497/b393497.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000</a>
%e A393497 For D = A003658(3) = 8, we have O_K = Z[sqrt(2)], and the fundamental unit epsilon = 1+sqrt(2) has norm -1. The order generated by units of norm 1 is Z[epsilon^2] = Z[3+2*sqrt(2)] = Z[2*sqrt(2)], so the index is 2.
%e A393497 For D = A003658(4) = 12, we have O_K = Z[sqrt(3)], and the fundamental unit epsilon = 2+sqrt(3) has norm 1. The order generated by units of norm 1 is Z[epsilon] = Z[sqrt(3)], so the index is 1.
%e A393497 For D = A003658(5) = 13, we have O_K = Z[(1+sqrt(13))/2], and the fundamental unit epsilon = (3+sqrt(13))/2 has norm -1. The order generated by units of norm 1 is Z[epsilon^2] = Z[(11+3*sqrt(13))/2] = Z[(1+3*sqrt(13))/2], so the index is 3.
%o A393497 (PARI) b(D) = my(w=quadunit(D)); if(norm(w)==-1, imag(w^2), imag(w))
%o A393497 for(D=2, 200, if(isfundamental(D), print1(b(D), ", ")))
%Y A393497 Cf. A003658, A014046 (index of the quadratic order generated by all units).
%K A393497 nonn
%O A393497 2,2
%A A393497 _Jianing Song_, Mar 22 2026
